# Test results
[Tt]est[Rr]esult*/
[Bb]uild[Ll]og.*
*.trx
*.coverage
*.coveragexml

# npm
# NOTE: npm/bin/mssql-mcp is intentionally NOT ignored. The committed file is a
# Node.js shim that makes `npx mssql-mcp` work immediately after install. The
# postinstall script (npm/install.js) overwrites it with the real native binary
# downloaded from GitHub Releases. Developers who run `npm install` locally will
# see `npm/bin/mssql-mcp` show as modified in git status — restore the shim with
# `git checkout -- npm/bin/mssql-mcp`. See ADR-0002 (sqz pattern) and ADR-0014.
npm/node_modules/
npm/bin/mssql-mcp.exe
npm/*.tgz

# Publish output
publish/
artifacts/

# Logs
*.log

# OS
Thumbs.db
Desktop.ini

# Local env files
.env
.env.local

# Azure SQL Edge (integration test data)
azure-sql-edge-data/

# Agent / AI tooling — local-only scratch, caches, and session state.
# These are per-developer working artifacts (issue drafts, ticket specs,
# knowledge-graph DBs, run continuations, skill caches) and must never be
# committed. .codegraph/ ships its own .gitignore that ignores everything
# except itself; the line here is a belt-and-suspenders fallback in case
# that file is ever removed.
.scratch/
.codegraph/
.omo/
.opencode/
.opencode.json
.opencode.jsonc
opencode.json
opencode.jsonc

# Other AI coding assistants (defensive — none are used in this repo today,
# but if a contributor opens it with one, their private state stays private).
# Per-assistant instruction files (AGENTS.md, CLAUDE.md, .cursorrules) are
# treated as personal config, not project source.
AGENTS.md
.claude/
CLAUDE.md
.cursor/
.cursorrules
.aider*
.codex*
.continue/
.windsurf/
codeium*
.tabnine*

# Local SQLite databases (AI tooling artifacts, never commit)
umans-gate*
*.db
*.db-shm
*.db-wal
